    "narrative": "The focal point of today\u2019s lineup is **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 83.29. He is in a prime position to capitalize against McCullers Jr., benefiting from a significant 16% park boost and a generous 19% SP skill advantage. With a slow delivery from the opposing pitcher boosting his already elite stolen base upside, **Gunnar Henderson** is the clear anchor of our offensive production. Close behind him is **Jacob Wilson**, whose 74.08 score reflects a massive +10% park factor and the security of leading off against a vulnerable southpaw. Both **Gunnar Henderson** and **Jacob Wilson** are essential targets for maximizing our speed and run production, especially in a landscape where stolen bases are at a premium.\n\nWhile our starters are locked in, **Nasim Nunez** represents the most precarious start of the day at 47.72. His inclusion is driven almost entirely by the situational opportunity against Peralta; despite a low floor, the 92% SB success rate against the opposing battery makes him a necessary evil to keep our stolen base category competitive. He barely edged out our depth options, as the optimizer prioritized his specific speed profile over the higher raw power outputs typical of players like **Coby Mayo** or **Miguel Vargas**, who remain benched today. We are currently monitoring **Drake Baldwin** at 54.14; while he is a marginal play, his placement in the #2 hole provides just enough lineup insulation to warrant the start, though we must remain cautious of his negative SP skill variance against Valdez.\n\nLooking ahead, the roster remains heavily impacted by inactivity from **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Andy Pages**, and **Jackson Merrill**, all of whom are either on the IL or off today, placing a heavy burden on our active bats to compensate. We are maintaining a watch on **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Josh Lowe** for potential pinch-hit opportunities if late-game weather shifts or defensive replacements create gaps in our 5x5 metrics. Provided the wind holds at our hitter-friendly venues, the combination of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**\u2019s elite xwOBA and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**\u2019s platoon-aided 60.56 score gives us a high probability of outperforming the raw projections.",
